==English==

===Etymology===
From [[cliff]] + [[hang]] + [[-er]], evoking the image of someone left hanging from a cliff, thereby having an uncertain [[fate]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-cliffhanger.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''cliffhanger'''
# An [[end]]ing or [[stop]]ping point calculated to leave a [[story]] unresolved, to create [[suspense]]
#:''[[w:Stephen King|Stephen King's]] novel [[w:The Waste Lands|''The Waste Lands'']] ended in a terrible cliffhanger.''

